Beginner Level

Problem 1: Person class with private fields, constructor, getters/setters → Encapsulation, Constructor, Getters/Setters.

Problem 2: BankAccount with deposit/withdraw and balance validation → Encapsulation, Methods, Validation, Exception handling.

Problem 3: Student class overriding toString() → Method Overriding, Polymorphism.

Problem 4: Rectangle class with area and perimeter → Method Design, Object Modeling.

Problem 5: Printable interface and Document class → Interfaces, Polymorphism.

Problem 16: Calculator with method overloading → Compile-time Polymorphism, Method Overloading.

Problem 17: Counter showing static vs instance members → Static vs Instance scope, Class vs Object variables.

Intermediate Level

Problem 6: Animal hierarchy (abstract class → Dog/Cat) → Abstract Classes, Inheritance, Method Overriding, Polymorphism.

Problem 7: Library system with List<Book> composition → Composition, Encapsulation, Collection Management.

Problem 8: Shape interface with Circle/Square → Interfaces, Polymorphism, Dynamic Dispatch.

Problem 9: Inventory system with ArrayList → Encapsulation, Collections, Method Logic.

Problem 10: Singleton ConfigManager → Singleton Pattern, Lazy Initialization, Global Access.

Problem 20: Day enum with isWeekend() → Enums, Encapsulation, Methods in Enums.

PRO Level

Problem 11: Employee hierarchy with Payable interface → Interfaces, Abstract Classes, Inheritance, Polymorphism, Method Overriding.

Problem 12: Plugin architecture → Interfaces, Polymorphism, Loose Coupling, Dynamic Behavior.

Problem 13: Mini game engine (Entity, Player/NPC, Updatable, Event Dispatcher) → Abstract Classes, Interfaces, Polymorphism, Modular Design.

Problem 14: Custom collection class implementing Iterable → Generics, Iterable/Iterator, Encapsulation.

Problem 15: Multi-layered banking model (Accounts, Transactions, Services) → Factory & Strategy Patterns, Composition, Inheritance, Polymorphism.

Problem 18: Inner / Nested classes → Inner/Nested Classes, Scope, Encapsulation.

Problem 19: Anonymous classes & Lambda expressions → Anonymous Classes, Lambda Expressions, Functional Interfaces.

Problem 21: Observer Pattern → Behavioral Pattern, Event-driven design, Loose Coupling.

Problem 22: Builder Pattern → Fluent API, Optional Parameters, Object Construction Pattern.

Problem 23: Thread-safe BankAccount → Concurrency, Synchronized Methods, Thread-safe Encapsulation.